== Preview Page - Preview of Automation Script Generation ==

The web search commands generated by the Preview button on the Preview Page in Automation Wizard are, if so desired, all the tasks to be carried out by the [[PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/Web Search Automation Process|Web Search Automation Process]] in PlanoTse.

{{PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/comingsoon}}

=== Input Fields ===

==== Browser Count ====
This specifies the maximum number of browser programs your computer can handle without freezing the screen.

==== Maximum Runs ====
This field specifies the number of web addresses the web automation session will navigate before stopping the session. Zero means limitless. This is useful for debug purposes.

==== Launch ASAP ====
Do you want to launch the browser ASAP, i.e. right after a web search command is generated? This field is not too useful at this time.

==== Internet Timeout ====
The system will keep trying to access the Internet until after this many seconds.

== Demo Section ==

{{message box|image=Right-pointing hand in green octagon.svg|backgroundcolor=Azure |heading=Demo Instruction - Part 1 of 2|message=For a demo do the following steps:
# If not already done, do all steps in the Demo Instruction at the bottom of the page, [[PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/Exclusion Page|Exclusion Page]].
# Leave all fields along and do not make any changes to the current input values.
# Press the PREVIEW button.
# Read the following text then do the steps in the Demo Instruction - Part 2 of 2
<span style="font-size:x-small;">This demo instruction is one in a series that begins on this page, [[PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/Automation Wizard|Automation Wizard]].</span>}}

The PREVIEW button does not do anything except to let  you know what is coming down the road. After pressing the PREVIEW button, you should see the following results on the whiteboard:
{{TextBox|
# { web search Banking Dallas job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
# { web search Retail Dallas job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
# { web search Banking Houston job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
# { web search Retail Houston job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
# { web search Banking San-Antonio job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
# { web search Retail San-Antonio job-description management -hardware -resume ; }
}}

There are <span style="font-size:medium; color:crimson; font-weight:bold;">6</span> web search command lines because you have 3 cities and 2 industries. This is the multiplicative effect of previously declared search factors. In another example, if you have 2 cities, 3 industries and 4 skills, the result would be 2 x 3 x 4 = 24 web search commands.

In this example, the above four web search commands would look for management jobs in two industries at two different cities. For good measure, hardware and resume were declared to be exclusion words. This mean that you would be get any articles that include any of these excluding words.

{{message box|image=Right-pointing hand in green octagon.svg|backgroundcolor=Azure |heading=Demo Instruction - Part 2 of 2|message=For a demo do the following steps:
# If not already done, do all steps in the Demo Instruction - Part 1 of 2, above.
# For this demo, place <span style="font-size:medium; color:blue; font-weight:bold;">5</span> in the field '''Browser Counter'''. This is important for the next page in this demo.
# Press the NEXT button.
# Go to the next topic in this book: [[PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/Generation Page|Generation Page]]
<span style="font-size:x-small;">This demo instruction is one in a series that begins on this page, [[PlanoTse Handbook for Job Search Automation/Automation Wizard|Automation Wizard]].</span>
}}


